{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@interface"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object. Configure the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"’s or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"’s polygons collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" method. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"text":" objects with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object from an array of coordinates."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"title":"MLNPolygon","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference"},{"text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertices, specified as ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances, and the edges that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"],"type":"inheritsFrom"},{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherited By","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"],"type":"inheritedBy"},{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Shapes","anchor":"Shapes","iden